<p>An explosion tore through the Plastmass military manufacturing plant in Kopeysk, Chelyabinsk region, on Wednesday, killing at least ten people and injuring others as emergency teams worked at the scene [bbc.com#1][rt.com#1]. Officials said a second blast occurred at the site and were checking reports of missing persons while medical teams treated the wounded [rt.com#1]. Russian outlets later gave a higher toll, with state-linked reporting saying the death count may have reached 12 and five injured, an update carried by international wire services [straitstimes.com#1]. Authorities said the incident did not appear to be linked to drone attacks and posed no threat to city residents or wider infrastructure, according to regional officials [rt.com#1].</p><h3>Highlights:</h3><ul><li>official updates: Chelyabinsk governor Aleksey Teksler initially gave a lower casualty figure before raising the toll as rescue and medical teams continued their work at the scene [rt.com#1].</li><li>video evidence: Footage obtained and circulated from the site shows a large fireball rising over the facility at the moment of the blast, offering visual confirmation of the scale of the explosion [rt.com#1].</li><li>regional context: Officials publicly noted concerns about recent cross-border drone strikes in Russian regions, saying investigators were treating this event as separate while those wider security tensions remain a backdrop [rt.com#1].</li></ul><h3>Perspectives:</h3><ul><li>Chelyabinsk regional governor Aleksey Teksler: He reported the initial casualty figures and said emergency services were working at the site while adding there was no threat to city residents or surrounding infrastructure. (<a href='https://www.rt.com/russia/626840-russia-explosion-chelyabinsk/'>RT</a>)</li><li>Local witnesses: Witnesses described seeing explosions and a large fireball at the Plastmass plant, providing immediate on-the-ground accounts of the blast. (<a href='https://www.bbc.com/news/articles/ckgzx82p1x5o'>BBC</a>)</li><li>Russian state-linked media (Izvestia): Izvestia reported a higher death toll of 12 and said five people were injured, a figure later picked up by international outlets. (<a href='https://www.straitstimes.com/world/europe/Death-toll-after-explosion-at-military-plant-in-Urals-city-kills-twelve-Russian-news-outlet-reports'>The Straits Times (citing Izvestia)</a>)</li></ul><h3>Sources:</h3><ul><li><a href='https://www.bbc.com/news/articles/ckgzx82p1x5o'>Ten dead in blast at Russian munitions plant in Urals</a> - bbc.com</li><li><a href='https://www.rt.com/russia/626840-russia-explosion-chelyabinsk/'>Russian industrial facility hit by deadly explosion (VIDEO)</a> - rt.com</li><li><a href='https://www.reddit.com/r/worldnews/comments/1odwrpd/explosion_at_russian_military_plant_kills_twelve/'>Explosion at Russian military plant kills twelve, media report</a> - reddit.com</li><li><a href='https://www.straitstimes.com/world/europe/Death-toll-after-explosion-at-military-plant-in-Urals-city-kills-twelve-Russian-news-outlet-reports'>Death toll after explosion at military plant in Urals city kills twelve, Russian news outlet reports</a> - straitstimes.com</li></ul>